      <h1>Privacy Policy for LOMO Pad</h1>
      <p class="meta"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> April 10, 2026</p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how LOMO Pad ("we," "us," or "our") handles information when you use the
        LOMO Pad application (the "App") on iOS and macOS.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information Collection and Use</h2>
      <p>
        We do not collect, store, or transmit personal data to our servers.
        LOMO Pad is designed to work entirely within your local network environment.
        The App does not require an internet connection to function, and we do not use third-party analytics,
        crash reporting, advertising, or user tracking services.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Local Network Usage</h2>
      <p>
        LOMO Pad requires access to your local network (including Wi-Fi or peer-to-peer local connections)
        in order to discover and connect your iOS device to your macOS host device.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Purpose:</strong> This permission is used only to transmit trackpad gestures and keyboard input
          from your iPhone or iPad to your Mac.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Data Handling:</strong> Control data is transmitted only within your local network connection.
          We do not receive, collect, or store your input data, gesture data, or network information.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        LOMO Pad does not integrate with third-party services that collect user data.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
        If we make changes, we will post the updated Privacy Policy on this page and revise the
        "Effective Date" at the top.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Contact Us</h2>
